top.value: The project aimed to build the capacity of the Office of the Ombudsman’s to better resolve complaints of corruption against public officials, and strengthen the Department of Justice’s capacity to conduct improved criminal prosecutions.
Proposed civil society organizations identified for support in each country; people living with HIV and members of key affected populations.

The project aimed to enable Montenegrin judges to deal more effectively and independently with competition, intellectual property cases, insolvency, maritime law, company law and consumer protection disputes, with a particular focus on the practice of courts in the EU.
To strengthen capacity and integrity of institutions to combat corruption, deliver justice, and to improve public services

1. To assist the EBRD in organising and holding the Judicial Training Conference (the “Conference”) on Insolvency Matters; Collaborate closely with, and to the satisfaction of, the EBRD Project Team and counterparts for the Conference, i.e. the HCC and the Academy.

1. To advise on and assist in the establishment of a Mediation Centre at the Chamber; 2. To provide support to the Centre for a six month period following its establishment; 3. To gather data on the effectiveness of the Centre during the six month period; 4. To assist the General Council of Courts of Mongolia (GCC) to extend its case management system to cover court-annexed mediation; 5. To work closely with a second consulting firm retained by the Bank which shall be responsible for training, workshops, an empirical study of the six month period, and the promotion of results (the “Second Consultant”); and 6. To strengthen the effective use of mediation for the resolution of business disputes in Mongolia
